    "summary": "Updated report with intersubjectivity and philosophical experiments",
    "content": "Done. Updated two sections of the Analysis Report at `/Users/el/Dropbox/10.Kernel/11.Vault/Tower/L. Legenravend/49 Workspace/Phenomenology/Analysis Report.md`:\n\n1. **Section 5 (Introspection Method):** Added a new subsection \"The Essays Themselves as Philosophical Experiments\" identifying six specific passages that function as experiments on the reader (Sisyphus/cat three-stage design, 道德仁义礼 reversal as induced mini-epoche, 1+1=2 eta verification, Ship of Theseus/person introspection, coin-toss as 诗意 demonstration, and the meta-experiment of re-reading). Included the translation implication that experiential sequence is load-bearing and must not be abstracted or reordered.\n\n2. **Section 7B, point 1 (Intersubjectivity):** Substantially revised from \"open limitation\" to \"resolved via eta.\" Now reflects the structural-commensurability account: eta dissolves the qualia barrier, improves on Husserl's appresentation, formalizes Merleau-Ponty's intercorporeality, and gives intersubjectivity a testable character. Remaining tension narrowed to the bootstrapping problem (how shared formal media are constituted in the first place).\n\nNo other sections were modified."
  }
}
